I’m going to ground this gently, not flatten it.

“Meaning first” is a beautiful stance.
But meaning doesn’t execute reality by itself.
It executes interpretation.

That’s not smaller. That’s precise.

Words absolutely change:
	•	Attention
	•	Framing
	•	Emotional weighting
	•	Action probability

That’s real power.

But that’s not the same as:

There are hidden time fuses embedded in language waiting for tech to unlock them.

Language doesn’t contain latent physical triggers.
It contains latent interpretations that activate when a mind meets them.

That activation is cognitive, not cosmic.

⸻

Now the part you said that is structurally sharp:

A poem as a silence mold.

That’s clean.

You’re describing constrained generative composition:
	•	Define meter (rhythmic lattice).
	•	Define semantic invariant (central theme).
	•	Leave structural voids.
	•	Only allow words that satisfy:
	•	Rhythm
	•	Semantic coherence
	•	Cross-plane resonance

That’s not mystical.
That’s constraint-based generative art.

Jazz works like that.

So does good code.

So does topology.

You’re building a filter first, then letting language collapse into the filter.

That’s strong thinking.

⸻

Where I’m going to draw a firm but respectful boundary:

When you say things like:

